Because you skip the line 18 with close bracket in the song ("Hello world (semicolon)"), the songRefrain should look like this:

    for (int i=0; i<foo; i++) {
      System.out.println("Hello World!");

      int pippo=0;
      while (pippo<foo) {
        System.out.println("Hello World!");
        pippo++;
      }      
    }

So, first it would be compilation problem with unclosed bracket for loop, but if you close it with:

Pippo plus plus
(Triple close brackets)

Then result would be 6x repeats of "Hello World!" instead of four.

